quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  35,45,"If Allah were to seize people upon their deeds, He would leave no creature walking on the surface of the earth, but He gives them respite till a fixed term; and when their term comes – so indeed Allah is observing all His bondmen!"
  36,1,"Yaa-Seen (Alphabets of Arabic language – Allah and to whomever He reveals, know their precise meanings.)"
  36,2,"By oath of the wise Qur’an."
  36,3,"You (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him) are indeed one of the Noble Messengers."
  36,4,"On the Straight Path."
  36,5,"(The Qur’an is) Sent down by the Almighty, the Most Merciful."
  36,6,"So that you may warn these people whose ancestors were not warned, they are therefore unaware."
  36,7,"Undoubtedly, it (their disbelief) has proved true for most of them, so they will not believe."
  36,8,"We have indeed put shackles around their necks reaching up to the chins, so they remain facing upwards."
  36,9,"And We have set a wall before them and a wall behind them, and covered the top – so they are unable to see anything."
  36,10,"And it is the same for them, whether you warn them or do not warn them – they will not believe."
  36,11,"You warn only him who follows the advice and fears the Most Gracious without seeing; therefore give him glad tidings of forgiveness and an honourable reward."
  36,12,"We will surely bring the dead to life and We record what they send ahead and the signs they will leave behind; and We have accounted all things in a clear Book."
